# UI Title Case

Use **Title Case** for all static user-facing **headings** (`h1`–`h3`, dialog titles, section titles), **button labels**, **form labels** (`Label`, checkbox labels), **filter trigger labels** (`emptyLabel`), and **icon-button `aria-label`s**.

## Rules

- Capitalize the first and last word.
- Capitalize major words; lowercase articles (`a`, `an`, `the`), conjunctions (`and`, `or`, `but`), and short prepositions (`in`, `on`, `at`, `to`, `for`) unless they are the first word — except keep prepositions capitalized when they are part of a fixed control name (e.g. `Filter By Focus`).
- Use `&` and `/` as in the source phrase (`Sync & Admin`, `Timing & Liquidity`).
- **Do not** title-case: API/data values, placeholders with examples (`politics,weather`), toast sentences, empty-state body copy, or dynamic content from the server.

## Examples

| ❌ Avoid | ✅ Prefer |
| -------- | --------- |
| `Sync event` | `Sync Event` |
| `Clear filters` | `Clear Filters` |
| `Agent export preview` | `Agent Export Preview` |
| `Yes bid` | `Yes Bid` |
| `Mark as stale` | `Mark As Stale` |
| `Open admin dialog` | `Open Admin Dialog` |
